[32m+[m[32m## Relationship to Architectural Distillation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe Factor Skyline is one instance of **[Architectural Distillation](https://github.com/allen-proxmire/architectural-distillation)** (AD), a general methodology for extracting structure from systems composed of interacting mechanisms. AD provides the concepts (channels, envelopes, constraint surfaces, poles) and the step-by-step process; FS is a specific mathematical theory produced by applying that process to the multiplicative structure of the integers.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Upstream methodology:** FS was originally developed alongside AD, which now lives in its own [dedicated repository](https://github.com/allen-proxmire/architectural-distillation). AD defines the general distillation process; FS inherits its architectural vocabulary from AD.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Downstream output:** FS represents one fully developed mathematical architecture produced using AD. The definitions, propositions, proofs, invariants, and reproducibility harness in this repository are the domain-specific mathematical content — the product of the distillation, not the methodology itself.[m
[32m+[m
